        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 22 at 11:39PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1139 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles southeast of Fritch, or 12 miles southwest of Borger, moving
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Borger and Skellytown.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
